((priv_mode == VU) && !(henvcfg.CBCFE && senvcfg.CBCFE)))
{
  <raise virtual-instruction exception>
}
// execute instruction
else
{
  <execute CBO.CLEAN or CBO.FLUSH>
}
Finally, a CBO.ZERO  instruction executes or raises an illegal-instruction or virtual-instruction exception
based on the state of the xenvcfg.CBZE  bits:
// illegal-instruction exceptions
if (((priv_mode != M) && !menvcfg.CBZE) ||
    ((priv_mode == U) && !senvcfg.CBZE))
{
  <raise illegal-instruction exception>
}
// virtual-instruction exceptions
else if (((priv_mode == VS) && !henvcfg.CBZE) ||
         ((priv_mode == VU) && !(henvcfg.CBZE && senvcfg.CBZE)))
{
  <raise virtual-instruction exception>
}
// execute instruction
else
{
  <execute CBO.ZERO>
}
Each xenvcfg register is WARL; however, software should determine the legal values from the execution
environment discovery mechanism.
